commitResults.messageTitle: Update code to allow for save
Update code to allow for save
commitResults.messageBody:
Bot refreshers with each load.

Users will not be able to use the bot effectively as data has to be
re-entered every load.

Let's save the user's input when assigning tasks to the bot.

Bot will now be able to reference the saved inputs and load the user's
saved data.

commitResults.messageTitle: Update bot to understand date and time
commitResults.messageBody:
There is no fixed format to the input for by, from and to. Bot is able
to accept any input and store them as a valid date and time.

Let's introduce LocalDateTime to the bot to enforce a specific input
format for the date and time input.

This minimises the random behaviour of the bot as any incorrect inputs
will be rejected by the bot.

commitResults.messageTitle: Update code to be more OOP
commitResults.messageBody:
The code works as intended.

Code can be further extracted to improve OOP.

Extracting the common behavior into a super class allows us to use
polymorphism when dealing with command attributes.

Let's extract and group similar commands in to various classes that
extends the parent class Command.

This improves readability and allows for inheritance as well.

Code was organised due to OOP, but can be further organised into
packages.

Let's group the classes into various functionalities and sort them
into the corresponding packages.

This avoids name conflict and helps with writing a better maintainable
code.

Code is working for manual inputs.

Let's use JUnit to automate the test cases.

This allows for a quicker check of the code when making small tweaks
and not have the need to manually input the same inputs each time.

commitResults.messageTitle: Package the app as an executable file
commitResults.messageBody:
Bot is now a working prototype.

Let's package it into a JAR file to be executed.

Remote access of the app is now available with this executable file.

Most methods, less the getters and setters, classes and fields now have
Javadocs comments to detail the function of said methods, class and
fields.

commitResults.messageTitle: Update code to follow coding standard
commitResults.messageBody: Let's update the code to follow the java coding standard.

commitResults.messageTitle: Update code to allow for find command
commitResults.messageBody:
Let's implement a find command to filter through the task list and
return a new list of task containg the keyword.

Several test cases are added for more extensive testing.
